Dialogue: 0,1:03:53.19,1:03:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, so that knowledge,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:55.36,1:03:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,the knowledge then is experiential.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:57.44,1:03:59.96,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not academic, it's not intellectual.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.80,1:04:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because you have been that and are that, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:08.48,1:04:11.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so I just wanted to emphasize why the repetition,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.15,1:04:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,people say, well, you said that before.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:16.80,1:04:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, where were we?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:21.78,1:04:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I can't read anything, I can't see nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:24.36,1:04:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Where are we, where are we?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.21,1:04:31.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'm glad those are big letters.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.51,1:04:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see that.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:34.26,1:04:41.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, oh, golly, was, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.50,1:04:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The experience of, without being edited,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.90,1:04:48.51,Default,,0,0,0,,we say that the ego jumps in and edits everything
Dialogue: 0,1:04:48.51,1:04:51.01,Default,,0,0,0,,within 1 10,000th of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.21,1:04:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And how do you get, and I call that the experiencer,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.17,1:04:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:59.00,1:05:01.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you get beyond that?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.84,1:05:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,The, what the mind does is like a tape recorder.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.86,1:05:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,There's the, let's say the birds are singing outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:10.57,1:05:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's the recording of the birds
Dialogue: 0,1:05:12.65,1:05:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that are singing outside.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:14.51,1:05:16.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Then on the old fashioned tape monitor,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:18.28,1:05:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,now in the old fashioned tape recorder,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:20.46,1:05:24.36,Default,,0,0,0,,there's a tape out monitor, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.36,1:05:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So the tape out monitor, you hear what's just been recorded.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:30.82,1:05:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So you see there's a disparity.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.57,1:05:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,There's what's happening.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.71,1:05:37.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there's the quick recording of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:37.88,1:05:42.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the tape out is of what you just taped.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:42.19,1:05:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can see what you've just taped is recorded.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.23,1:05:49.19,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's what the ordinary mind does.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.19,1:05:52.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What you're hearing, hearing is the recording.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:52.80,1:05:58.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Once you go past the experiencer to the spontaneous,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:59.88,1:06:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,once you're past the experiencer, all, you hear all birds as they,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:05.07,1:06:08.80,Default,,0,0,0,,the bird sounds without having the bird recorded.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:08.80,1:06:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you hear the recording of the bird in your mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.38,1:06:15.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So you hear the source rather than the recording
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.07,1:06:16.69,Default,,0,0,0,,of the source.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:16.69,1:06:22.05,Default,,0,0,0,,That recording happens in one 10,000th of a second.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.05,1:06:22.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:22.90,1:06:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,So in letting go all of the things that you let go of
Dialogue: 0,1:06:28.76,1:06:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,on the evolutionary path, there comes the,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.01,1:06:39.28,Default,,0,0,0,,there comes the time when you are, you are that, that with,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:39.28,1:06:42.09,Default,,0,0,0,,that with what, what is,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:42.09,1:06:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,However, whether than that, which has just been recorded
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.71,1:06:47.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's what,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:47.44,1:06:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what is blinding because that's what reveals Divinity.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.36,1:06:54.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And it takes quite a while to get over
Dialogue: 0,1:06:54.07,1:06:59.30,Default,,0,0,0,,the shock of the shock I called reality shock.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:00.19,1:07:05.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It takes years, frankly, years before he can function.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:05.28,1:07:06.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Again.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:06.19,1:07:08.11,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:08.11,1:07:11.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So you really live with reality of, of, isn't this,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:11.21,1:07:15.23,Default,,0,0,0,,of existence, of what is, without having any editing.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:16.28,1:07:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't say to yourself, it's good or it's bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:20.86,1:07:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,When you're just living with what is,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:22.88,1:07:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,your mind doesn't say, isn't that beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.96,1:07:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds stupid, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:27.53,1:07:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that beautiful?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.69,1:07:33.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Like seeing the Taj Mahal and saying,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:34.01,1:07:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,wow, isn't that pretty?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:38.30,1:07:41.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Taj Mahal is beyond being pretty.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:41.84,1:07:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It's beyond being beautiful.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:44.19,1:07:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Its reality is stunning.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.13,1:07:48.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Its reality is stunning, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:49.55,1:07:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Or in one of the Great Pyramids or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.00,1:07:56.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And there's various entities around the Great Pyramids,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.36,1:07:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.88,1:07:59.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You hang out there and you visit them.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:59.46,1:07:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Yep.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:04.01,1:08:07.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, that's gone on in the Great Pyramids, I'll tell you.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.07,1:08:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a great place to meditate all night.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.67,1:08:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Cost you a few bucks.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:12.65,1:08:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The guards become friendly, slip my 10 or 20,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:23.18,1:08:26.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can meditate all night in the Great Pyramid.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.26,1:08:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And you'll make sure nobody else comes in and invades your privacy.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:31.43,1:08:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish to be alone.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.05,1:08:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten bucks, you got it all night.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.90,1:08:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.07,1:08:47.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, so that's tape out versus recording.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.92,1:08:49.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.02,1:08:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, the mind, left to its own device, has no check on reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.47,1:08:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,So the human, you can have compassion for the human,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:59.77,1:09:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,because the human is like the old sailor trying to sail the seas without a compass.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:05.98,1:09:07.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No sextant, no compass.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:08.71,1:09:10.17,Default,,0,0,0,,They sail by dead reckoning.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.47,1:09:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And I think by dead reckoning, what, at the bottom of the Great Lakes?
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.63,1:09:19.40,Default,,0,0,0,,There are 6,000 ships at the bottom of the Great Lakes.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:20.18,1:09:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,So at the bottom of the sea floor,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.75,1:09:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you're littered with tens of thousands of sailors who, at that time, did not have a compass.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.38,1:09:32.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's the predicament of the human mind.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:33.19,1:09:38.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The predicament of the human mind is it doesn't have any external point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:39.21,1:09:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no GPS positioning system.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.22,1:09:46.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So you can be wacky and loony and totally out of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.60,1:09:51.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And everybody can see it, but you can't see it because you don't have a compass that says,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:51.77,1:09:53.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you're 80 degrees off this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:54.31,1:09:55.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You're 80 degrees this way.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:59.77,1:10:04.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So the human dilemma then, compassion arises for human ignorance, et cetera,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:05.36,1:10:08.36,Default,,0,0,0,,because the mind has no point of reference.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.19,1:10:12.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And anybody can understand from scientific learning,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:13.61,1:10:18.03,Default,,0,0,0,,without a point of reference, there is no way of knowing anything about anything
Dialogue: 0,1:10:19.03,1:10:21.34,Default,,0,0,0,,within the world that we call reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:24.78,1:10:28.32,Default,,0,0,0,,That was the value I saw of the calibrated levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:29.27,1:10:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,But for the first time, mankind had an external source of reference,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:34.07,1:10:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of verification of the truth or falsehood, of any concept, thing, idea, place, position,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:40.93,1:10:43.67,Default,,0,0,0,,personality, point of view, whatever.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:45.05,1:10:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,For the first time, man had a compass.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.84,1:10:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, man has never had a compass.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:50.92,1:10:55.65,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no way man has ever been able to know the truth of anything he believes.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:56.18,1:10:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,No way.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:57.84,1:11:00.38,Default,,0,0,0,,He had faith in the Inca gods.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:00.38,1:11:03.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Or he had faith in the spirit of the volcano.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:03.64,1:11:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Or, you know, he placed it in wild animals, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:08.18,1:11:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But those were just belief systems.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:12.00,1:11:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Man has never had any means of discerning truth and falsehood.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.17,1:11:20.63,Default,,0,0,0,,It's staggering that man got this far, you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:22.84,1:11:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Mainly he didn't, however.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:25.85,1:11:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,All you see is the megal tail of what did make it.
