Dialogue: 0,1:24:09.39,1:24:11.85,Default,,0,0,0,,No, what he said is money trumps peace
Dialogue: 0,1:24:11.85,1:24:13.14,Default,,0,0,0,,or oil trumps peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.14,1:24:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,That calibrates at 365.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:15.85,1:24:18.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, Bush said it.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:18.53,1:24:20.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Money or oil, I forget, trumps peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:20.72,1:24:21.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.72,1:24:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.73,1:24:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.89,1:24:21.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:21.96,1:24:22.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.07,1:24:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.18,1:24:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.26,1:24:22.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.34,1:24:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.43,1:24:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.46,1:24:22.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.57,1:24:22.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.72,1:24:22.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.77,1:24:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.81,1:24:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:22.97,1:24:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.01,1:24:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.05,1:24:23.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.10,1:24:23.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.14,1:24:23.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.21,1:24:23.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.27,1:24:23.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.60,1:24:23.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.64,1:24:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.71,1:24:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.75,1:24:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:23.81,1:24:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Functionally, functionally.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:26.68,1:24:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, narcissism therefore warps and distorts.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:31.72,1:24:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything gets politicized,
Dialogue: 0,1:24:34.03,1:24:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,narcissistically warped and distorted
Dialogue: 0,1:24:37.00,1:24:38.57,Default,,0,0,0,,so that it's self-serving.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:38.57,1:24:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's all self-serving, the perpetrator-victim role.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.43,1:24:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And the reason people cling to it
Dialogue: 0,1:24:45.01,1:24:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is they love to picture themselves as victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:49.00,1:24:53.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm, victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:53.82,1:24:55.81,Default,,0,0,0,,It's funny we don't have any mad feminists
Dialogue: 0,1:24:55.81,1:24:57.67,Default,,0,0,0,,getting up here and jumping on the stage.
Dialogue: 0,1:24:57.67,1:25:04.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Depriving them of feeling persecuted
Dialogue: 0,1:25:04.89,1:25:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and martyred and put down
Dialogue: 0,1:25:08.94,1:25:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,when they've had the upper hand all along for God's sake.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:14.64,1:25:15.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Eve was no fool.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:15.61,1:25:17.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, ha, ha, ha.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:17.53,1:25:19.53,Default,,0,0,0,,She's had it her way ever since.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:20.89,1:25:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:22.61,1:25:26.35,Default,,0,0,0,,All information, no matter how seemingly correct,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:26.35,1:25:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is always presumptive.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:27.96,1:25:31.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So wisdom, part of a spiritual evolution,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:32.50,1:25:34.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is the development, progression,
Dialogue: 0,1:25:34.64,1:25:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and development of wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:37.38,1:25:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing that is important to learn
Dialogue: 0,1:25:39.22,1:25:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,is that all information and all knowledge
Dialogue: 0,1:25:41.38,1:25:43.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and everything you think and believe
Dialogue: 0,1:25:43.22,1:25:45.94,Default,,0,0,0,,is presumptive only.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:45.94,1:25:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And that it may, it's subject to change later.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:49.05,1:25:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything you know, think, or believe is provisional.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:53.97,1:25:55.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything is provisional.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:55.73,1:25:58.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's presumptive and provisional.
Dialogue: 0,1:25:58.34,1:26:03.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So with wisdom, you learn to hold back a certain degree
Dialogue: 0,1:26:03.22,1:26:05.80,Default,,0,0,0,,and more will be added later.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:08.57,1:26:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, all the years since World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:26:12.53,1:26:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,and many of the things that happened in World War II
Dialogue: 0,1:26:14.96,1:26:16.92,Default,,0,0,0,,that were extremely critical
Dialogue: 0,1:26:16.92,1:26:19.23,Default,,0,0,0,,are only coming to light now.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:19.23,1:26:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,50 or so, nine years later, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:21.93,1:26:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that the Japanese had almost perfected
Dialogue: 0,1:26:23.97,1:26:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,an atomic bomb wasn't even known
Dialogue: 0,1:26:26.43,1:26:31.18,Default,,0,0,0,,until the papers of some Japanese physicists
Dialogue: 0,1:26:31.18,1:26:34.92,Default,,0,0,0,,were made public in the mid-70s.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:34.92,1:26:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,American public didn't know it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:36.19,1:26:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody even knew it.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:37.19,1:26:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,They were just a couple of months away from an atomic bomb.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:40.14,1:26:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,They didn't know it was a bomb themselves anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:42.64,1:26:46.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was on History Channel or something like that.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:46.72,1:26:50.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So even though it seems like all has been known,
Dialogue: 0,1:26:50.14,1:26:52.48,Default,,0,0,0,,there is yet more to know.
Dialogue: 0,1:26:52.48,1:26:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So we then have a certain modesty about anything
Dialogue: 0,1:26:56.09,1:27:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,we think or believe because we know that more may be added
Dialogue: 0,1:27:00.47,1:27:02.39,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole picture may be changed.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:02.39,1:27:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All you need is one more piece of information
Dialogue: 0,1:27:05.43,1:27:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and the whole chessboard changes.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:06.94,1:27:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,You move the bishop from one square to this square,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:09.97,1:27:12.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole game just totally changed,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:12.22,1:27:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,moving one little piece of information.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:15.65,1:27:19.05,Default,,0,0,0,,All information is presumptive.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:19.05,1:27:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We already covered Yev by college.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:23.42,1:27:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And we covered Protagoras' dictum
Dialogue: 0,1:27:25.34,1:27:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that reality is purely a subjective presumption.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:30.52,1:27:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That is also a basic tenet of relativism,
Dialogue: 0,1:27:34.17,1:27:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that all information, et cetera, is only a point of view.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:38.86,1:27:43.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And there is no such thing as the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:43.06,1:27:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,No such thing as the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:45.13,1:27:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And once in a while, I get an indignant letter.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:47.64,1:27:51.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Somebody gets very indignant when I speak about the absolute
Dialogue: 0,1:27:51.75,1:27:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,because to relativism, there is no such thing as an absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:27:56.35,1:27:58.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's one reason there is no God
Dialogue: 0,1:27:58.27,1:28:02.03,Default,,0,0,0,,and there is no calibrated level of 1,000.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:02.03,1:28:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,There is no such thing as the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:04.07,1:28:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,We have one more chart on this, yeah, yes?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:08.93,1:28:14.57,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so absolutism is anathema to relativism.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:15.34,1:28:19.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It just ruins their sleep and everything else.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:19.88,1:28:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't eat, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:22.18,1:28:24.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Their life comes to an end.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:24.77,1:28:26.86,Default,,0,0,0,,That there is an absolute truth.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:30.52,1:28:34.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Why does it make them so bad, mad?
Dialogue: 0,1:28:34.32,1:28:37.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's because the narcissistic core, the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:37.10,1:28:39.81,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the last thing it wants to hear.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:39.81,1:28:43.35,Default,,0,0,0,,That there is something of greater sovereignty
Dialogue: 0,1:28:43.35,1:28:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,than the ego itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:46.53,1:28:48.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So the narcissistic core, the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:48.43,1:28:49.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So the narcissistic core, the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:28:49.14,1:28:51.26,Default,,0,0,0,,hates divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:28:51.26,1:28:53.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and it hates the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:54.07,1:28:56.14,Default,,0,0,0,,It hates calibrated levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,1:28:57.39,1:28:58.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It hates that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:00.42,1:29:01.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It just hates that.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:03.53,1:29:06.10,Default,,0,0,0,,The fact that a dog calibrates higher than people you know.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:08.92,1:29:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I can't read what that says,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:12.15,1:29:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,but whatever it says looks interesting.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:17.64,1:29:18.17,Default,,0,0,0,,What does it say?
Dialogue: 0,1:29:19.63,1:29:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Reality is a product of paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.43,1:29:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:22.82,1:29:27.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only is reality difficult, if not impossible, to ascertain,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:28.81,1:29:32.57,Default,,0,0,0,,every paradigm of reality is a different reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:33.72,1:29:35.18,Default,,0,0,0,,The different levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:29:35.18,1:29:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,are really different paradigms.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:39.14,1:29:42.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The difficulty with atheism and skepticism and all such things
Dialogue: 0,1:29:42.57,1:29:47.42,Default,,0,0,0,,is that the linear domain of causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:48.64,1:29:50.18,Default,,0,0,0,,the 400s,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:51.39,1:29:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the linear is one domain,
Dialogue: 0,1:29:53.53,1:29:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and the non-linear is another domain.
Dialogue: 0,1:29:57.65,1:30:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And the limited mind cannot grasp that there is a domain
Dialogue: 0,1:30:01.35,1:30:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and a context of context
Dialogue: 0,1:30:05.10,1:30:10.48,Default,,0,0,0,,that is greater than the pedestrian mundane world of logic.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:10.48,1:30:15.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So it cannot comprehend that there's any reality greater than itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:15.68,1:30:19.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So you'll notice skepticism, which calibrates very low, by the way,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:19.81,1:30:21.22,Default,,0,0,0,,because it's a form of nihilism.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:22.60,1:30:23.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Skepticism calibrates very low.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:24.56,1:30:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And it does so because it thinks the only reality
Dialogue: 0,1:30:27.64,1:30:31.73,Default,,0,0,0,,is content and linear causality,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:31.73,1:30:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and it doesn't realize that there's anything that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:30:34.93,1:30:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond consciousness to the level of the 400s.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:39.11,1:30:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks that, you know, if you can't prove it, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:43.52,1:30:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So it poo-poos religion and faith and all these things.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:47.77,1:30:49.28,Default,,0,0,0,,But as we've mentioned before,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:49.60,1:30:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,the one thing that skepticism has tremendous faith in
Dialogue: 0,1:30:53.02,1:30:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is its own self.
Dialogue: 0,1:30:55.22,1:30:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The skeptic ridicules faith,
Dialogue: 0,1:30:59.94,1:31:02.86,Default,,0,0,0,,but it has profound faith in its own convictions
Dialogue: 0,1:31:02.86,1:31:05.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and its own skepticism.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:06.31,1:31:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So that is the paradox, really, Protagoras' paradox.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:12.71,1:31:15.98,Default,,0,0,0,,The absolute truth is unknowable,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:16.85,1:31:22.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and the skeptic definitely has faith in the truth of that statement,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:22.14,1:31:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,that the absolute truth is unknowable.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:25.22,1:31:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If it's unknowable, then what the skeptic is saying
Dialogue: 0,1:31:27.82,1:31:30.56,Default,,0,0,0,,has no basis in reality whatsoever, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:32.02,1:31:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.11,1:31:34.26,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:34.89,1:31:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:37.42,1:31:38.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Are we down to the last page?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:39.03,1:31:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I want to make sure I do more.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:41.65,1:31:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:42.19,1:31:43.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the last page?
Dialogue: 0,1:31:44.19,1:31:46.57,Default,,0,0,0,,We might have some time where we can jabber a few minutes.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:47.47,1:31:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Share it with the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:49.40,1:31:50.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll hurry up.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:55.77,1:31:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice women are not repressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:31:57.56,1:31:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, all she has to do is raise her voice,
Dialogue: 0,1:31:59.47,1:32:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,and I scurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:00.85,1:32:01.34,Default,,0,0,0,,You know what I'm saying?
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.06,1:32:04.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Repressed women.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:04.93,1:32:05.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, right.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:07.61,1:32:12.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In their imagination, they like to play victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:14.77,1:32:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the narcissistic ego loves to be victim.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:17.89,1:32:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It loves to be victim, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:19.82,1:32:23.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll tell you what, it's not better that way either.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:25.64,1:32:29.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We said that all reality is presumptive versus provable.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:30.32,1:32:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't prove any reality whatsoever.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:33.85,1:32:34.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Marx said,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:35.27,1:32:36.64,Default,,0,0,0,,religion is the opiate of the people,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:37.22,1:32:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,people wonder why relativism and far leftism is atheistic,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:42.85,1:32:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is because it's Marxism, and Marx was an atheist.
Dialogue: 0,1:32:47.94,1:32:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Didn't they ever hear the quote,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:50.27,1:32:52.14,Default,,0,0,0,,religion is the opiate of the people,
Dialogue: 0,1:32:54.18,1:33:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,therefore all Marxism and its various intellectual disguises is atheistic.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:02.55,1:33:07.60,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a basic principle which denies the reality of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:08.27,1:33:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,It denies the reality of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:09.13,1:33:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So Marxism denies the reality of the absolute.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:14.80,1:33:18.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And religion is the opiate of the people.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.09,1:33:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:20.56,1:33:26.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Relativistic antagonism towards the absolutism of religion.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:26.36,1:33:26.55,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,1:33:27.40,1:33:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:30.61,1:33:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Tolerance is a very fashionable word,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:35.35,1:33:39.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's really a downward slope to non-reality.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:40.39,1:33:42.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Because tolerance is now applied to everything,
Dialogue: 0,1:33:42.93,1:33:48.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that has been traditionally unacceptable.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:48.38,1:33:52.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We should be tolerant to everything, tolerant to everything.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:52.86,1:33:57.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So I suggest you're welcome to be tolerant to anything you like.
Dialogue: 0,1:33:57.96,1:34:02.75,Default,,0,0,0,,But don't include me in.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:02.75,1:34:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:06.07,1:34:09.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the Komodo dragon is still a Komodo dragon.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:09.02,1:34:13.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If we're nice to the Komodo dragons, they won't bite you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:13.02,1:34:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,No, they won't.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:14.82,1:34:23.30,Default,,0,0,0,,The Komodo dragons won't bite people.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:23.30,1:34:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The way they get to heaven is by killing you.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:27.14,1:34:30.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That's our little secret.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:30.43,1:34:34.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Step into my cage and you're bare feet, you're safe.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:34.88,1:34:39.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So tolerance then becomes a form of ignorance, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:34:39.52,1:34:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:41.19,1:34:44.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The world's afraid to call a spade a spade anymore
Dialogue: 0,1:34:44.80,1:34:51.10,Default,,0,0,0,,for fear of this political splatter.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:51.10,1:34:55.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nobody wants to call a spade a spade.
Dialogue: 0,1:34:55.47,1:34:56.88,Default,,0,0,0,,If somebody's out to kill you, that's pretty, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:34:56.88,1:34:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,let's not pretend it is due to a deprived childhood
Dialogue: 0,1:34:59.81,1:35:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,when the speaker is a multimillionaire.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:03.23,1:35:10.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The warning given by Bin Laden, see?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:10.68,1:35:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The meaning of it was missed by the world, you know?
Dialogue: 0,1:35:14.47,1:35:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,If you read the Koran, the Koran says,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:18.35,1:35:25.06,Default,,0,0,0,,first you offer them to convert, and then if they refuse,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:25.06,1:35:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,you are justified to kill them.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:27.31,1:35:28.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, when you come home, you must go home.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:28.43,1:35:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.81,1:35:29.85,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.85,1:35:29.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:29.92,1:35:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.10,1:35:30.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.23,1:35:30.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be prepared.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:30.26,1:35:37.48,Default,,0,0,0,,When Bin Laden invited America to convert to Islam,
Dialogue: 0,1:35:37.48,1:35:41.03,Default,,0,0,0,,you've been invited.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:41.03,1:35:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, if you don't, we can kill you
Dialogue: 0,1:35:44.25,1:35:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,with a free conscience.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:47.64,1:35:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The significance of that was missed by everybody
Dialogue: 0,1:35:50.35,1:35:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,in the press, et cetera.
Dialogue: 0,1:35:53.06,1:35:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The reason he invited America to convert to Muslimism
Dialogue: 0,1:36:00.57,1:36:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is because that's the opening gambit.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:03.51,1:36:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And after all, they invented chess.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:07.55,1:36:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And I myself was once a pretty champion chess player.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:11.86,1:36:16.21,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got his bishop trapped already six moves ahead of him
Dialogue: 0,1:36:16.21,1:36:18.85,Default,,0,0,0,,by moving this knight here.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:18.85,1:36:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,And I move my knight here, I got his bishop
Dialogue: 0,1:36:22.06,1:36:24.22,Default,,0,0,0,,about five moves down and he can't get out of it
Dialogue: 0,1:36:24.22,1:36:28.46,Default,,0,0,0,,because I already got this black with my knight.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:28.46,1:36:36.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If I say to you, you're all invited to convert,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:36.47,1:36:39.18,Default,,0,0,0,,now it's on your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:39.18,1:36:41.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Your death is on your head.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:41.10,1:36:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You understand that chess moves.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.02,1:36:45.68,Default,,0,0,0,,The people are,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:45.68,1:36:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they're way ahead of us in playing chess.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:49.42,1:36:51.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Our side is pretty dumb.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:51.06,1:36:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Doesn't even recognize an obvious move.
Dialogue: 0,1:36:53.81,1:36:56.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you see them move his bishop over like that,
Dialogue: 0,1:36:56.06,1:36:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for Christ's sake?
Dialogue: 0,1:36:58.18,1:37:00.07,Default,,0,0,0,,He just moved.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:00.07,1:37:02.19,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just women having their way.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:07.96,1:37:12.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Women have their way with men, if you know what I mean.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:12.42,1:37:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So sexism works both ways.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:15.46,1:37:19.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So a lot of these politicalizations, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:19.36,1:37:20.51,Default,,0,0,0,,lend themselves so readily to humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:20.51,1:37:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think humor is one of the most healing modalities.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:27.67,1:37:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I think it's very supportive of spiritual evolution
Dialogue: 0,1:37:32.75,1:37:35.60,Default,,0,0,0,,because many things you really can't get beyond
Dialogue: 0,1:37:35.60,1:37:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because of the ambiguity.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:37.21,1:37:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, humor then brings out the ambiguity.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:40.22,1:37:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And because humor brings out the ambiguity,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:42.56,1:37:46.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see the fallacy and laugh at it.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:46.38,1:37:50.60,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you're very serious, you have committed suicide by now.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:51.89,1:37:54.63,Default,,0,0,0,,If you live to a respectable old age.
Dialogue: 0,1:37:54.63,1:37:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,So the first requirement to become a member of the octogenarians,
Dialogue: 0,1:37:59.92,1:38:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,of which I am present, is a sense of humor.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:05.76,1:38:10.42,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of humor about anything and everything, you see.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:10.42,1:38:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of humor is necessary for longevity.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:14.00,1:38:18.81,Default,,0,0,0,,All the people who lack it are probably six feet under already
Dialogue: 0,1:38:18.81,1:38:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,because they took everything seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:20.93,1:38:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. I used to take things seriously.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:23.77,1:38:24.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I told you how I did.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:24.92,1:38:25.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to go to the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.11,1:38:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to go to the doctor.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:25.23,1:38:29.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I had to go for treatment for scrupulosity.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:29.18,1:38:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,My mother would call up to the bedroom.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:30.81,1:38:33.35,Default,,0,0,0,,She'd say, are you dressed, ready to go yet?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:33.35,1:38:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd say, yes, mom, I'll be right down.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:35.64,1:38:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I still had one sock and one shoe to put on.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:38.97,1:38:40.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, yes, mom, I'll be right down.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:40.64,1:38:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,I quickly put them on.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:41.52,1:38:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I run down the stairs.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:42.81,1:38:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Instantly, I'm hit with guilt that I lied to my mother.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:46.42,1:38:47.73,Default,,0,0,0,,She said, are you ready to go?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:47.73,1:38:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And I said, yes, and I still had one shoe and one sock.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:51.81,1:38:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,So literally, it was a lie, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:38:55.18,1:38:59.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'd had that guilt until I got to confession.
Dialogue: 0,1:38:59.75,1:39:01.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mary's and five of our fathers.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:01.14,1:39:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the priest would say, you know,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:05.10,1:39:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you don't need to feel guilty about every little trivial
Dialogue: 0,1:39:07.72,1:39:08.35,Default,,0,0,0,,thing, so.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:08.35,1:39:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the other side of no conscience
Dialogue: 0,1:39:14.23,1:39:16.53,Default,,0,0,0,,is too much conscience.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:16.53,1:39:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Scrupulosity.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:17.69,1:39:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So a sense of humor prevents scrupulosity.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:21.89,1:39:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Because I want everybody to take everything spiritually
Dialogue: 0,1:39:24.69,1:39:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,seriously, but not to the point of scrupulosity,
Dialogue: 0,1:39:28.65,1:39:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and still have a sense of humor about it.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:30.57,1:39:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So I think that's what I'm trying to do with this.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:33.02,1:39:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:34.69,1:39:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,What happens next?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:35.69,1:39:36.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick break.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.19,1:39:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:36.92,1:39:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll line up questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:38.92,1:39:42.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we take a quick break.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:42.03,1:39:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we'll have questions and answers.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:44.03,1:39:47.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And then after that, I get to shake everybody's hand?
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.14,1:39:47.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, good.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:47.64,1:39:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,OK.
Dialogue: 0,1:39:48.14,1:39:50.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounded like a jolly afternoon.
